Introduction

This is a digest of results from a battery of accessibility Tests.

The battery includes 1353 automated accessibility tests drawn from ten different packages: Alfa, Axe, Continuum, Equal Access, HTML CodeSniffer, Nu Html Checker, QualWeb, Tenon, Testaro, and WAVE.

These tests were run on the web page named above and gave the page a score of 1908, where 0 would be perfect.

Issue summary

Special issues

log: Score 563. This is based on the amount of browser error logging and miscellaneous logging during the tests.

solos: Score 34. This is based on issues reported by unclassified tests. Details are in the report.

Classified issues

Issue contentBeyondLandmarks

WCAG: 1.3.6

Score: 363

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r57, score 340 (Perceivable text content is not included in any landmark)
  • Package axe, test region, score 34 (Some page content is not contained by landmarks)
  • Package ibm, test Rpt_Aria_OrphanedContent_Native_Host_Sematics, score 18 (Content does not reside within an element with a landmark role)

Issue textContrastAA

WCAG: 1.4.3

Score: 296

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r69, score 203 (Text outside widget has subminimum contrast)
  • Package axe, test color-contrast, score 81 (Element has insufficient color contrast)
  • Package ibm, test IBMA_Color_Contrast_WCAG2AA, score 128 (Contrast ratio of text with background does not meet WCAG 2.1 AA)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R37, score 1 (Text has less than the minimum contrast)
  • Package wave, test c:contrast, score 18 (Very low contrast)
